legacy.full_text:
Cold Email 101

Over the past month, I've closed 5 clients with cold emails alone.

Want to know a secret?

I used the same 5 techniques every time.

Thread

legacy.description: I will get you more clients with Cold Email | Harvard Grad '16 | Founder of https://t.co/wdP8BAFYA7
legacy.name: Ben Rasmussen

legacy.full_text:
Technique #1: Personalized Openers

How it works:

1. Research the client's recent success.
2. Start the email with a genuine compliment.
3. Keep it short and sweet.

This simple technique makes your email stand out.

legacy.description: I will get you more clients with Cold Email | Harvard Grad '16 | Founder of https://t.co/wdP8BAFYA7
legacy.name: Ben Rasmussen

legacy.full_text:
Technique #2: Value-Driven Pitch

How it works:

1. State a clear benefit they'll get.
2. Show a brief success story.
3. End with a call to action.

Quick note: Don't do hard selling.

That's a mistake. This soft pitch works better.

legacy.description: I will get you more clients with Cold Email | Harvard Grad '16 | Founder of https://t.co/wdP8BAFYA7
legacy.name: Ben Rasmussen

legacy.full_text:
Technique #3: Follow-Up

How it works:

Avoid sending "Just checking in".
Send a fresh value tip instead.
If you offer fresh value, you'll get their attention again.

Easy, right?

legacy.description: I will get you more clients with Cold Email | Harvard Grad '16 | Founder of https://t.co/wdP8BAFYA7
legacy.name: Ben Rasmussen

legacy.full_text:
Technique #4: Social Proof

How it works:

1. Mention a happy client.
2. Share a quick win from that client.
3. Show a mini-testimonial.

Do these 3 things, and they'll trust you more.

legacy.description: I will get you more clients with Cold Email | Harvard Grad '16 | Founder of https://t.co/wdP8BAFYA7
legacy.name: Ben Rasmussen

legacy.full_text:
Technique #5: Clear Next Steps

How it works:

1. Offer a short, free consultation.
2. Set a direct time for the call.
3. Make it easy for them to say yes.

That's it.

legacy.full_text:
Use these 5 techniques to close more clients:

1. Personalized Openers
2. Value-Driven Pitch
3. Solid Follow-Up
4. Use Social Proof
5. Give Clear Next Steps

Get out there and win some clients.
